'''亚利桑那州'''

2018年3月18日晚间，在亚利桑那州坦佩市(Tempe)，一辆自动驾驶的Uber汽车撞死一名穿越马路的行人<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://gbiz.caixin.com/2018-03-20/101223534.html|title=Uber自动驾驶汽车撞死行人 未来发展仍非坦途|accessdate=2018-03-20|archive-date=2020-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200822023454/http://gbiz.caixin.com/2018-03-20/101223534.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。这是全球首例自动驾驶汽车导致人类死亡的事故。当地警方公布死者是49岁的赫茨伯格（Elaine Herzberg），车上有一名安全员司机，当时坐在驾驶位置，并未在事故中受伤。事故发生时，遇难者从车辆前部左侧阴影处推着自行车出现，车辆未做出减速或者避让措施<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://twitter.com/TempePolice/status/976585098542833664|title=Tempe Police Vehicular Crimes Unit is actively investigating the details of this incident that occurred on March 18th. We will provide updated information regarding the investigation once it is available.pic.twitter.com/2dVP72TziQ|accessdate=2018-03-22|date=2018-03-21|last=Police|first=Tempe|work=@TempePolice|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201215203701/https://twitter.com/TempePolice/status/976585098542833664|dead-url=no}}</ref>，可能在自动驾驶决策方面存在问题。警方公布录像显示，安全员也存在失职行为，当时他在车内低头看着屏幕，未尽到瞭望职责。

肇事汽车是一款沃尔沃XC90 SUV。美国国家公路交通安全管理局（National Highway Traffic Safety Administration）在向路透社发表的一份声明中表示，该机构“正在就此事件与优步、沃尔沃、联邦当局、州和地方当局进行接触”，并将采取适当行动。

2019年3月5日，[[亚瓦派|亚瓦派]]检察官在一封公开信中表示，优步不用承擔這起無人駕駛汽車死亡事故的刑事责任<ref>{{cite web|url=http://auto.huanqiu.com/globalnews/2019-03/14481878.html?agt=61|title=全球首起自动驾驶致命事故认定：优步无刑事责任|publisher=|accessdate=2019-03-07|archive-date=2019-03-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190308003004/http://auto.huanqiu.com/globalnews/2019-03/14481878.html?agt=61|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

====加拿大====
2012年9月，一篇溫哥華商業媒體的文章報導優步和當地法規之間的爭議<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biv.com/article/20120918/BIV0112/309189915/-1/BIV/ride-for-hire-alternative-enters-market|title=Ride-for-hire alternative enters market|publisher=Business In Vancouver|date=2012-09-18|accessdate=2012-12-12|language=en|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130518033239/http://www.biv.com/article/20120918/BIV0112/309189915/-1/BIV/ride-for-hire-alternative-enters-market|archivedate=2013-05-18}}</ref>。2012年11月22日，優步宣布在溫哥華將結束「秘密優步」（Secret Uber）的試營運階段，並將費率提高為每小時[[加幣|加幣]]75元以符合當地的法規<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.techvibes.com/blog/uber-to-raise-minimum-charge-for-a-ride-to-75-ubervanlove-2012-11-22|title=Uber to Raise Minimum Charge for a Ride to $75|publisher=Techvibes|date=2012-11-22|accessdate=2012-12-12|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121128122303/http://www.techvibes.com/blog/uber-to-raise-minimum-charge-for-a-ride-to-75-ubervanlove-2012-11-22|archive-date=2012-11-28|dead-url=yes}}</ref>。截至2012年12月，優步尚未在溫哥華申請執照<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biv.com/article/20121204/BIV0118/312049911/black-sedan-service-hits-regulatory-speedbump|title=Black sedan service hits regulatory speedbump|publisher=Business In Vancouver|date=2012-12-04|accessdate=2012-12-05|language=en|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130718094149/http://www.biv.com/article/20121204/BIV0118/312049911/black-sedan-service-hits-regulatory-speedbump|archivedate=2013-07-18}}</ref>。

2012年12月5日，[[多倫多|多倫多]]市政府官員指控優步違反25項地方規範，包括無執照計程車仲介和無照禮車服務等<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/1298266--uber-taxi-charged-with-licensing-offences|title=Taxi app company Uber charged with licensing offences|publisher=Toronto Star|date=2012-12-05|accessdate=2012-12-05|language=en|archive-date=2013-01-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130115005101/http://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/1298266--uber-taxi-charged-with-licensing-offences|dead-url=no}}</ref>。多倫多政府關於表示他們曾建議優步依照當地法規營運。優步的競爭應用程式已在當地取得執照<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2012/10/18/uber-a-lone-rogue-in-toronto|title=Uber: A Lone Rogue in Toronto|publisher=Toronto Sun|date=2012-10-18|accessdate=2012-12-05|language=en|archive-date=2020-10-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201020091940/https://torontosun.com/2012/10/18/uber-a-lone-rogue-in-toronto|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 計費與付款方式 ==
優步的計費方式與[[计价器|按表收費]]的計程車不同，一般計程車使用特製里程表收費，但優步直接使用設備上的GPS計價，且計算費率和收款都由優步負責，駕駛並未參與其中。當優步車輛以超過{{convert|11|mph}}的速度行駛時，是以距離計價。在其他時候則是以時間計價<ref>{{cite news | url=http://vator.tv/news/2011-12-07-uber-pulls-in-another-32m-for-app-based-car-service | title=Uber pulls in another $32M for app-based car service | work=VatorNews | date=2011-12-07 | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2012-01-07 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107212620/http://vator.tv/news/2011-12-07-uber-pulls-in-another-32m-for-app-based-car-service | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。在每次搭乘結束後，旅程的費用將直接從乘客登記的信用卡中扣款。除了「Uber Taxi」的一般計程車服務之外，扣款的費用在預設時並不包含小費，而優步也在官方網站和應用程式中註明「不需要支付小費」<ref name="techcrunch.com" />。優步曾表示較高的收費是因為其提供更可靠、更準時，且更舒適的服務<ref name="nytimes.com"/><ref>{{cite web | url=http://blog.uber.com/2011/04/11/uberdata-the-hidden-cost-of-cabs/ | title=Uberdata: The Hidden Cost of Cabs | publisher=Uber | work=Uber Blog | date=2011-04-11 | author=voytek | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2014-10-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141018070658/http://blog.uber.com/2011/04/11/uberdata-the-hidden-cost-of-cabs/ | dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://techcrunch.com/2011/03/02/a-week-with-uber-and-this-blogger-is-totally-hooked/ | title=A Week With Uber And This Blogger Is Totally Hooked | publisher=AOL | work=TechCrunch | date=2011-03-02 | author=Arrington, Michael | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2019-08-16 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190816150346/https://techcrunch.com/2011/03/02/a-week-with-uber-and-this-blogger-is-totally-hooked/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

在例如萬聖節、跨年夜或天氣不佳（如風雪或大雨）等叫車需求較高的時段，優步將會實施「加成計費」（surge price）提高價格以吸引更多駕駛來達到[[經濟均衡|經濟均衡]]<ref name=kelly2011 /><ref>{{cite news | last=Harris | first=David | title=That time Uber almost charged me $1,099 for a Boston-to-Cambridge trip | date=2014-04-24 | url=http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/blog/techflash/2014/04/my-1-099-uber-trip-from-boston-to-cambridge.html | work=Boston Business Journal | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2014-04-25 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140425130728/http://www.bizjournals.com/boston/blog/techflash/2014/04/my-1-099-uber-trip-from-boston-to-cambridge.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。優步也會在極端的天氣狀態下實施加成計費，例如大多倫多地區在2013年7月8日造成淹水的暴風雨，以及紐約市[[颶風珊迪|颶風珊迪]]來襲期間<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.techvibes.com/blog/uber-toronto-activates-surge-pricing-during-storm-2013-07-09 | title=Uber Toronto Activates Surge Pricing During Storm, Triggering a Bad PR Storm of Its Own | work=Techvibes.com | date=2013-07-09 | agency=Techvibes | author=Thomas, Knowlton | language=en | access-date=2014-08-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008220826/http://www.techvibes.com/blog/uber-toronto-activates-surge-pricing-during-storm-2013-07-09 | archive-date=2014-10-08 | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。當加成計費實施時，顧客在預約車輛前會看見特別通知<ref name="kelly2011">{{cite web | url=http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/10/27/is-uber-really-a-good-alternative-to-taxis/ | title=Is Uber Really a Good Alternative to Taxis? | publisher=Lockergnome | work=LockerGnome | date=2011-10-27 | author=Clay, Kelly | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2012-01-02 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120102160727/http://www.lockergnome.com/social/2011/10/27/is-uber-really-a-good-alternative-to-taxis/ | dead-url=yes }}</ref>。在2011年的[[跨年|跨年]]期間，部分地區的優步加成費率達到普通費率的七倍，引起許多乘客的不滿<ref name="nyt-nye">{{cite news | url=http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/01/08/disruptions-taxi-supply-and-demand-priced-by-the-mile/ | title=Disruptions: Taxi Supply and Demand, Priced by the Mile | work=Bits | date=2012-01-08 | agency=The New York Times Company | author=Bilton, Nick | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2012-01-18 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118175132/http://bits.blogs.nytimes.com/2012/01/08/disruptions-taxi-supply-and-demand-priced-by-the-mile/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。優步的共同創辦人崔維斯·卡蘭尼克回應：「⋯因為這項服務太新了，需要一段時間讓大家接受它。計程車固定費率的情況已經持續了70年<ref name="nyt-nye" />。」

==迴響和評價==
===美國===
美國企業家[[馬克·安德森|馬克·安德森]]在2011年表示他將十分願意投資優步。他告訴[[CNET|CNET]]「優步是一個吞噬計程車的應用程式⋯其有著殺手級的體驗。你可以在地圖上看到預定的車輛正向你開來<ref>{{cite news | url=http://news.cnet.com/8301-1023_3-57345138-93/marc-andreessen-predictions-for-2012-and-beyond/ | title=Marc Andreessen: Predictions for 2012 (and beyond) | work=CNET News | date=2011-12-19 | agency=CBS Interactive | author=Sloan, Paul | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2013-12-12 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131212184857/http://news.cnet.com/8301-1023_3-57345138-93/marc-andreessen-predictions-for-2012-and-beyond/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>。」此外在2011年，《[[紐約時報|紐約時報]]》形容優步「聰明但所費不貲」，指出車隊有著「優秀的一致性品質標準」，但乘車前的等待時間較傳統紐約市的計程車和出租車來得久<ref name="nytimes.com">{{cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/15/nyregion/uber-and-weeels-offer-car-services-by-phone-app.html?_r=1 | title=The Smartphone Way to Beckon a Car | work=The New York Times | date=2011-05-16 | author=Brustein, Joshua | language=en | accessdate=2014-08-14 | archive-date=2020-09-28 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200928134649/https://www.nytimes.com/2011/05/15/nyregion/uber-and-weeels-offer-car-services-by-phone-app.html?_r=1 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

《[[今日美國|今日美國]]》在2013年將優步選為該報的年度科技公司<ref>{{cite news|last1=Wolff|first1=Michael|title=Wolff: The tech company of the year is Uber|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/money/columnist/wolff/2013/12/22/the-success-of-app-based-car-service-uber/4141669/|accessdate=2014-06-13|publisher=USA Today|date=2013-12-22|language=en|archive-date=2020-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809151401/https://www.usatoday.com/story/money/columnist/wolff/2013/12/22/the-success-of-app-based-car-service-uber/4141669/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

優步同時也面臨包括「[[Lyft|Lyft]]」和「[[SideCar|SideCar]]」等低成本[[即時共乘|即時共乘]]新創公司的競爭，因此優步推出「優步計程車」（UberTaxi）和「菁英優步」（UberX）服務，前者與當地的計程車公會合作，後者則是使用非豪華的轎車車型載客<ref>{{cite web |url=http://techcrunch.com/2012/07/01/uber-opens-up-platform-to-non-limo-vehicles-with-uber-x-service-will-be-35-less-expensive/ |title=Uber Opens Up Platform To Non-Limo Vehicles With “Uber X,” Service Will Be 35% Less Expensive |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2012-07-01 |accessdate=2014-01-24 |language=en |archive-date=2020-10-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201028122354/https://techcrunch.com/2012/07/01/uber-opens-up-platform-to-non-limo-vehicles-with-uber-x-service-will-be-35-less-expensive/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。這個舉動讓一些優步禮車的司機感到不滿，認為此舉造成他們收入的減少<ref>{{cite web |url=http://techcrunch.com/2013/03/15/see-uber-this-is-what-happens-when-you-cannibalize-yourself/ |title=See, Uber — This Is What Happens When You Cannibalize Yourself |publisher=TechCrunch |date=2013-03-15 |accessdate=2014-01-24 |language=en |archive-date=2020-08-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200809131031/https://techcrunch.com/2013/03/15/see-uber-this-is-what-happens-when-you-cannibalize-yourself/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

===香港===
優步推出「關懷優步」(uberASSIST)服務，得到社福機構支持，旗下司機已學懂基本[[手語|手語]]、折疊輪椅等技巧。長者、傷健人士、行動不便者的乘客都可透過手機應用程式，預訂接載服務<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.skypost.hk/%E6%B8%AF%E8%81%9E/%E6%96%B0%E8%81%9E%E9%A0%AD%E6%A2%9D/20160219/001/%E5%BE%8B%E5%B8%AB%EF%BC%9A%E4%BB%8D%E5%B1%AC%E9%81%95%E6%B3%95%20Uber%E5%8F%B8%E6%A9%9F%E5%8F%97%E8%A8%93%E8%BC%89%E5%82%B7%E5%81%A5%E8%80%85/206990 | title=律師：仍屬違法 Uber司機受訓載傷健者 | date=2016-02-19 | publisher=[[晴報|晴報]] | language=zh-hk }}{{dead link|date=2017年11月 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>。

聾人機構「[[龍耳|龍耳]]」指出，曾有聾人遇上[[香港的士|的士]]司機不熟路，無法溝通，最後去錯目的地，故聾人通常要靠其他人協助召車。[[香港失明人協進會|香港失明人協進會]]視障會員表示，在街道截乘的士很困難，常被他人搶先上車，就算電召的士，交代司機在哪裡上落車也不容易。優步得悉傷健人士的困難後，遂與龍耳、香港失明人協進會及[[香港耀能協會|香港耀能協會]]康復專業學院合作，向參與「關懷優步」的司機提供培訓。社福機構認為新科技為長者及殘疾人士帶來方便<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.am730.com.hk/article-302445 | title=談司機被定罪 堅稱已購保險 Uber新服務助老弱傷殘 | date=2016-02-19 | publisher=[[AM730|AM730]] | language=zh-hk | accessdate=2016-02-19 | archive-date=2016-02-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160222122622/http://www.am730.com.hk/article-302445 | dead-url=no }}</ref>。

另一方面，部分團體關注Uber的安全和法律責任問題，由於它在香港屬非法載客取酬，汽車交通運輸業總工會的士司機分會就批評Uber在不受保障下載客，猶如在道路埋下炸彈，影響其他道路使用者。他們要求當局加強執法打擊，一方面保障乘客和司機安全，一方面保障的士司機收入<ref name="mingpao0422"/>。

2020年8月，Uber建立網站 https://www.regulateuber.hk {{Wayback|url=https://www.regulateuber.hk/ |date=20200714125134 }} 以群眾力量就香港立法規管汽車共乘服務向香港政府施壓<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.regulateuber.hk | title=讓行政長官聆聽到你的聲音，支持立法規管汽車共乘服務 | date=2020-08-22 | publisher=[[Uber|Uber]] | language=zh-hk | accessdate=2020-12-18 | archive-date=2020-07-14 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200714125134/https://www.regulateuber.hk/ | dead-url=no }}</ref>

